# VCF 9.x Lab Environment Quick Reference

This is a **Holodeck nested virtualization lab** running VCF 9.0.x or 9.1.x. All passwords default to `/home/holuser/creds.txt`.

## Key Hostnames & Auth

| Component | Hostname | User | Auth |
| --- | --- | --- | --- |
| SDDC Manager | `sddcmanager-a.site-a.vcf.lab` | `vcf` | Basic Auth |
| VCF Operations | `ops-a.site-a.vcf.lab` | `admin` | OpsToken |
| vCenter (Mgmt) | `vc-mgmt-a.site-a.vcf.lab` | `administrator@vsphere.local` | Session |
| vCenter (WLD) | `vc-wld01-a.site-a.vcf.lab` | `administrator@wld.sso` | Session |
| NSX (Mgmt) | `nsx-mgmt-01a.site-a.vcf.lab` | `admin` | Basic Auth |
| NSX (WLD) | `nsx-wld01-01a.site-a.vcf.lab` | `admin` | Basic Auth |
| VCF Automation | `auto-a.site-a.vcf.lab` (10.1.1.70/71) | `vmware-system-user` | SSH+sudo |
| VSP Cluster CP | `10.1.1.142` (VIP) | `vmware-system-user` | SSH+sudo |

## Critical Reminders

- **SDDC Manager rotates passwords** â€” check `/v1/credentials` if standard password fails.
- **vCenter SSH host keys change on upgrade** â€” always use `StrictHostKeyChecking=accept-new`.
- **vapi-endpoint and trustmanagement often STOPPED** after boot â€” start via `vmon-cli --start`.
- **NSX user IDs are numeric** (`0`=root, `10000`=admin). NSX CLI password-expiration broken on 9.1 â€” use REST API.
- **Component CRDs are cluster-scoped** (`components.api.vmsp.vmware.com`) â€” never use `-A` or `-n` flags.
- **SSH escaping with kubectl** â€” use `-o json` parsed locally, never `custom-columns` through SSH layers.
- **VCF Automation microservice deployments** may remain at 0 replicas after shutdown â€” must be scaled up manually.
- **CSI service account passwords** (`svc-vcfsp-vc-*@vsphere.local`) can be rotated during VCF upgrades â€” reset via `dir-cli password reset` on vCenter.
- **VCF 9.0 vs 9.1**: OpsToken authSource is `local` (9.0) vs `localItem` (9.1). Password management API only exists in 9.1+. VCF Automation sudo is NOPASSWD (9.0) vs password-required (9.1).
- **SDDC Manager credential REMEDIATE** requires: (1) service accounts fixed in vCenter SSO first, (2) stale locks cleared from `platform.lock` table, (3) resource statuses set to ACTIVE in platform DB. Process one resource at a time (10-task concurrency limit).
- **SDDC Manager PostgreSQL** is on `127.0.0.1:5432` (TCP, not socket). Password in `/root/.pgpass`. SSH as `vcf` user can run `psql` without root.
- **SDDC Manager `/v1/resource-locks` API is read-only** â€” cannot DELETE locks via API. Must use direct `psql` access to `DELETE FROM lock`.
- **vCenter `/api/session` returns HTTP 201**, not 200. Accept both when checking session creation success.
- **SCP VMs are EAM-managed on VCF 9.0.x** â€” `PowerOnVM_Task()` via vCenter returns `NoPermission`. Connect directly to ESXi hosts as `root` to power on SCP VMs.
- **VCF Automation VIP (10.1.1.70) can drop after cold boot** â€” kube-vip releases the VIP when istio-ingressgateway has no endpoints (ImagePullBackOff during Antrea CNI init). Fix: `ip addr add 10.1.1.70/32 dev eth0`, restart containerd/kubelet, delete ImagePullBackOff pods. `VCFfinal.py` Task 4b automates this.
- **Supervisor kube-dns endpoint may point to LB IP** after ungraceful shutdown â€” causes vSphere Pod DNS to fail via asymmetric NSX DLB routing. Fix: patch endpoint to CoreDNS pod IPs (`172.16.200.x`). `VCFfinal.py` Task 2c2 automates this.
- **NSX Edge SR STANDBY having `Op_state: down` interfaces is normal** â€” in `ACTIVE_STANDBY` mode, only the ACTIVE SR brings up its interfaces. Check HA status via NSX Policy API `/policy/api/v1/infra/tier-1s/{id}/locale-services/{id}/ha-config` before diagnosing as broken.
- **NSX Edge VMs are registered on WLD ESXi hosts** (not management vCenter) â€” must connect directly to ESXi hosts as `root` to power on/off edge VMs. They're on `esx-06a` (edge-wld01-02a) and `esx-07a` (edge-wld01-01a).
- **VSP service CIDR is `198.18.128.0/17`** â€” not the standard `10.96.0.0/12`. Must include `198.18.0.0/16` in NO_PROXY for containerd/kubelet on VSP nodes, otherwise image pulls from the internal registry (`198.18.128.16:5000`) get routed through Squid proxy and fail with 403.
- **Fleet LCM direct API uses different type names** than suite-api proxy: `NI`â†’`OPS_NETWORKS`, `LI`â†’`OPS_LOGS`, `FLEET_LCM`â†’`VCF_FLEET_LCM`, `SDDC_LCM`â†’`VCF_SDDC_LCM`.
- **Fleet LCM shutdown returns HTTP 202** with a `taskId` â€” poll via `GET /fleet-lcm/v1/tasks/{taskId}`.
- **OpsToken authSource varies** in VCF 9.1 builds â€” try both `local` and `localItem`.

